        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 6:28PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Akela, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deming and Rock Hound State Park.

This includes Interstate 10 in New Mexico between mile markers 83 and
98.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
